# Loan Default Prediction

Exploring methods for predicting loan default risk using machine learning and credit score categorisation.
This project was completed as part of the **JPMorgan Chase Quantitative Research simulation** from Forage.

## Overview

This project investigates approaches to modelling loan default probability using borrower credit data. Two approaches are explored:

* Random Forest modelling of default probability, parameterised to accept customer details.
* Categorisation of FICO credit scores to analyse relationships with default risk.

## Scripts

| Script            | Description                                                                                                                                                  |
| :---------------- | :----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `threeDefProb.py` | Trains a Random Forest model to predict loan defaults and evaluates performance using AUC. Parameterised to accept customer details to generate predictions. |
| `fourFicoBin.py`  | Bins FICO credit scores into categories to analyse their relationship with loan default risk.                                                                |

## Methods

**Model:** Random Forest classifier
**Evaluation metric:** Area Under the ROC Curve (AUC)
**Feature exploration:** Credit score binning (FICO categories)

## Requirements

* Loan data table from the JPMorgan Chase Quantitative Research simulation

```python
pandas
numpy
scikit-learn
matplotlib
```

## Example Usage

```bash
python threeDefProb.py \
  --credit_lines_outstanding <value> \
  --loan_amt_outstanding <value> \
  --total_debt_outstanding <value> \
  --income <value> \
  --years_employed <value> \
  --fico_score <value>
```

```bash
python fourFicoBin.py
```

### Parameter Descriptions

* `credit_lines_outstanding` – Outstanding credit lines
* `loan_amt_outstanding` – Remaining loan amount
* `total_debt_outstanding` – Total outstanding debt
* `income` – Annual income
* `years_employed` – Total years of employment
* `fico_score` – Borrower FICO credit score

## Project Goals

* Explore predictive modelling of loan defaults
* Evaluate the usefulness of FICO score categorisation
